ities, including Piero Boitani, Roland Le Huenen, Rachel Adelman, and Christina Tarnopolsky. Students and experts in the humanities who desire a rich grounding in the concept of recognition should start with this book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aComparative literature. 0aKnowledge, Theory of, in literature. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aLittérature comparée. 0aLittératurexHistoire et critiquexThéorie, etc. 0aRecognition (Philosophy)xHistory. 0aRecognition in literature. 0aReconnaissance dans la littérature. 0aSubsomptionxHistoire. 0aThéorie de la connaissance dans la littérature. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aEssays.  aLiterary Criticism.  aPhilosophy.1 aAdelman, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoitani, Piero, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Harry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraybill, Rhiannon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLe Huenen, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMucignat, Rosa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeil Weiner, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRing, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRusso, Teresa G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRusso, Teresa G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSunkenberg, Jenna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTarnopolsky, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVaughan, Kevin Frederick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/